-- Mechel, Norilsk Nickel, VTB May Be Active: Russian Equity Market Preview
-- B y   D e n i s   M a t e r n o v s k y
-- 2010-10-05T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/mechel-norilsk-nickel-vtb-may-be-active-russian-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and share
prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock Micex Index added 0.7 percent to 1,465.09. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index rose 0.4 percent to 1,538.22.  OAO Mechel  (MTLR RX): Russia’s largest producer of coal for
steelmaking is scheduled to report its second-quarter financial
results. Company shares added 1.2 percent to 770.46 rubles.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel  (GMKN RX): Russia’s largest mining
company’s first-half net profit rose more than fivefold to $2.35
billion as metal prices surged, the Moscow-based company said in
a statement after markets closed. Company shares added 1.2
percent to 5,310.31 rubles.  AFK Sistema  (SSA LI): Billionaire  Vladimir Yevtushenkov ’s
holding company said Svyazinvest’s transfer of 28 percent of
shares in OAO Moscow City Telephone Network, or MGTS, to a
Sistema unit in exchange for a 50 percent stake in Sky Link has
been completed. Company shares added 0.5 percent to $26.40.  VTB Group  (VTBR RX): The supervisory board of Russia’s
second-biggest lender approved the planned purchase of 50
percent plus 1 share in OAO TransCreditBank by the end of the
year, Interfax reported, citing a source close to the board. The
bank will have a three-year option to boost its stake to 100
percent, according to Interfax. Shares rose 0.7 percent to 8.93
kopeks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Denis Maternovsky  in Moscow at 
